<span id="freeTextContainer9139291682145578839">A great reread! I first read this series back in my elementary days (a great x-mas gift!) and loved it! Years later, I learned that there were 3 more series following this one that dealt with the same characters. So I bought them all (BTW you can buy any of these author&apos;s books from his website and SIGNED for no additional cost!) and have gradually been rereading this first series in preparation of eventually reading the next ones. A fun, inspiring, and at times thought-provoking/soul searching </span>
  <span id="freeText9139291682145578839" style="display:none">A great reread! I first read this series back in my elementary days (a great x-mas gift!) and loved it! Years later, I learned that there were 3 more series following this one that dealt with the same characters. So I bought them all (BTW you can buy any of these author's books from his website and SIGNED for no additional cost!) and have gradually been rereading this first series in preparation of eventually reading the next ones. A fun, inspiring, and at times thought-provoking/soul searching story. I love how the author has merged elements of the King Aurther legend with dragons and with elements of Christianity. It's probably one of the most fun Christian/faith based reads I've come across since C.S. Lewis. With non-stop action and danger and DRAGONS, I think there is something here for everyone, child and adult alike. There's even some teenage romance, so yes, something for just about everyone. 🤭 I can't wait to read where these characters go next!</span>
  <a data-text-id="9139291682145578839" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

