        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer689694839" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10781023407210725197">I loved the entire &apos;Dragons In Our Midst&apos; series, and Tears of a Dragon was a great ending. The story was entertaining and I liked how the characters start to mature more. It ties up a lot of loose ends, but leaves open new mysteries for &apos;Oracles of Fire&apos; to solve. I also love how Bryan Davis always clearly shows how good conquers evil in the end. (SPOILER ALERT!) It was also satisfying that all the Dragons got a choice of how to become, and that Billy&apos;s father became human again. The emotions i</span>
  <span id="freeText10781023407210725197" style="display:none">I loved the entire 'Dragons In Our Midst' series, and Tears of a Dragon was a great ending. The story was entertaining and I liked how the characters start to mature more. It ties up a lot of loose ends, but leaves open new mysteries for 'Oracles of Fire' to solve. I also love how Bryan Davis always clearly shows how good conquers evil in the end. (SPOILER ALERT!) It was also satisfying that all the Dragons got a choice of how to become, and that Billy's father became human again. The emotions in all the characters felt so real, so it felt so good. (END OF SPOILER) This is a well-written book that you won't ever want to put down! You will surely want to read it.</span>
